The Minnedosa Chancellors finished third at the provincial high school girls’ rural soccer championship in Steinbach. 
Keeper Telecia Dowsett, defender Victoria Olson and midfielder Ashley Robinson were named all-stars as the Chancellors rebounded from a 2-1 loss to Steinbach in Saturday’s semifinals to top Morden 5-0 in the third-place game. The Minnedosa Chancellors finished third at the provincial high school girls’ rural soccer championship in Steinbach. 
Keeper Telecia Dowsett, defender Victoria Olson and midfielder Ashley Robinson were named all-stars as the Chancellors rebounded from a 2-1 loss to Steinbach in Saturday’s semifinals to top Morden 5-0 in the third-place game. Dauphin shut out Hapnot, which is from Flin Flon, 3-0 in the fifth-place game. Lorette beat Steinbach 3-0 in the final.
